<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={10.13}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={11.52}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={4.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={10.13}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={11.52}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>19.99</li><li>59.99</li><li>98.8</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}^{{2}}={10.13}^{{2}}+{11.52}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({10.13}\right)}{\left({11.52}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{16}={102.6169}+{132.7104}-{233.3952}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{219.3273}=-{233.3952}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.93972498149062}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={19.994578176397}={19.99}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({19.994578176397}\right)}}}}{{4.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{10.13}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2.3063966123038}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left({2.3063966123038}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={59.990308198458}\approx{59.99}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{19.994578176397}+{59.990308198458}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={98.796430055148}\approx{98.8}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

